## 🚨 Common Violations and Fixes

### ❌ Violation: Tailwind Color Classes

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG
<div class="border border-red-500">Error</div>
<div class="border-2 border-green-500">Success</div>
<div class="border border-blue-500">Info</div>
```

### ✅ Fix: Use Design System Colors

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<div class="border-destructive">Error</div>
<div class="border-thick-success">Success</div>
<div class="border-primary">Info</div>
```

### ❌ Violation: Inline Styles

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG
<div style={{ border: "1px solid var(--border)" }}>Content</div>
<div style={{ border: "2px solid var(--modus-wc-color-success)" }}>Content</div>
```

### ✅ Fix: Use Utility Classes

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<div class="border-default">Content</div>
<div class="border-thick-success">Content</div>
```

### ❌ Violation: Generic Tailwind Classes

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG
<div class="border border-gray-300">Content</div>
<div class="border-2 border-slate-400">Content</div>
```

### ✅ Fix: Use Design System Utilities

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<div class="border-default">Content</div>
<div class="border-thick-border">Content</div>
```

## 🔧 Linting and Validation

### Pre-commit Hooks

The project includes pre-commit hooks that automatically check for border violations:

```bash
# Manual linting
npm run lint:borders

# All linting checks
npm run lint:all
```

### Common Linter Messages

```text
❌ Found: class="border border-red-500"
✅ Use instead: class="border-destructive"

❌ Found: class="border-2 border-green-500"
✅ Use instead: class="border-thick-success"

❌ Found: style={{ border: "1px solid var(--border)" }}
✅ Use instead: class="border-default"
```

